President Obama has nominated Raymond Lohier, Jr. for the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit and Judge Kate O'Malley for the United States Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit. Lohier is currently an Assistant United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York and serves as Chief of the Securities and Commodities Fraud Task Force. O'Malley is a U.S. District Judge for the Northern District of Ohio and also teaches patent litigation at Case Western Reserve University School of Law. Both nominees have extensive legal backgrounds and are known for their commitment to fairness and judicial integrity.